<Content>I was deciding between the MuVo tx fm and the MuVo N200.  The basic difference between them is the N200 is smaller, lighter, lower cost, and has an input jack to record from an external source.  The Tx fm is slightly larger and heavier(but still very small and light in my opinion), and does not need a separate connector to hook up to the computer to download.  So for me it boiled down to an external input or convience to download.  Eventually over time I tend to misplace the external connectors so I chose the MuVo Tx FM.  So far I am very happy with it.  I just plug it in to download new music (I don't have to search for the extra cable).    It is kind of a pain as someone else mentioned to switch between FM and MP3, but I don't change over that often so it's not really a problem.  Amazon might filter this section out so I separated it.  It has to do with price and convience.  In the end I did not buy it from Amazon due to the price difference.  I had sent in several "found a cheaper price elsewhere" but the price was never adjusted.  I was also worried about service if it came D.O.A.  Amazon actually had the advantage there since they ship this product out of Office Depot, but the price difference almost paid for the extended service contract.  
