<Title>Great mp3 player for ppl who are active and want the basics
<Date>Mon Aug 01 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>There are a lot of mp3 players out there nowadays, and I think it's just a matter of finding the one with the features that you want/need for the best price...  What I like most about this mp3 player is the fact that it does not need xtra cables to transfer data files.  I also like the way it navigates, like how it uses the scroll wheel for skipping tracks, as well as a separate volume button (though some ppl might prefer the joystick-type controller that other players, e.g. iriver has).  It is very light, and since there are no internal moving parts, like all other flash players, it is highly appropriate for active tasks, such as working out.  The player is also great in that it has an FM tuner that works well.  One bad thing about the player: the backlight causes high-frequency background noise while a song might be playing... in other words, if you are playing a song, and decide to change the volume or change a setting, or switch to the next song, the backlight will turn on and you will hear a tiny noise in the background.  Of course, I don't really need the backlight on anyway, so I turned it off completely (this also conserves battery life ;) )  Overall, I've only had the player for a couple of days, but I am highly satisfied.  It is light, it is thin, it does not need cables, and it takes in standard AAA batteries that can be found anywhere.  
