<Date>Thu Sep 29 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>This thing is about the size and weight of a cigarette lighter, and yet holds a huge amount of music that is as simple as click-and-drag to load onto the thing.  It has a wonderful and easy-to-use menu system accessed by the toggle wheel.  The FM radio works really well and I have had no problems with reception.  I have not used the audio recorder part of it, but it is cool it has one.  It is astonishing to me that so much can come in such a small package.  Most importantly, it SOUNDS really good.  The sound I get through the earbuds seems better to me than my son's ipod shuffle.  For the money, I do not think this little thing can be beat.  
